int getNthTerm(int n) {
    if(n == 1) 
        return 0;
    if(n == 2)
        return -1; 
    if(n == 3)
        return -1;

    return getNthTerm(n-1) + getNthTerm(n-2) + getNthTerm(n-3);
}

int main() {
    int n;
    cout << "Enter n: ";
    cin >> n;

    cout << "The " << n << "th term is: " << getNthTerm(n);  
    return 0;
}
```

The logic is:
- Base cases: 
    - 1st term is 0
    - 2nd term is -1
    - 3rd term is -1
- Nth term = (n-1)th term + (n-2)th term + (n-3)th term

The getNthTerm() function implements this logic recursively.

